history.text: Hi
Hey. The movie is Mean Girls. I wouldn't see it unless you like Lindsey Lohan
Well, is it funny at least?
It's a teen comedy and based on a book called Queen Bees and Wannabees, so it might have some funny parts
I'm huge into books, but I haven't read Queen Bees and Wannabes. I'm not a huge fan of it, but I don't hate it, either. Are there any other known actors/actresses in it?
It also has Rachel McAdams in it
She was in the Notebook, wasn't she?
And Tina Fey was the screenplay writer
I'm not a huge fan of Tina Fey, but she might not be in it. And if she is...
I'm not sure if Rachel McAdams was also in the Notebook but the movie received a 66 out of 100 from Metacritic
Well, it's a teen movie, so I wouldn't assume she would have a huge role.
That's not bad for a movie rating, especially if there were a lot of reviews.
The screenplay was highly praised by critics in the Rolling Stone calling it "comic gold"
However, it is definitely geared towards teenagers
Just because it's geared towards teenagers, doesn't necessarily mean it's bad. BBC's "skins" was geared toward teens but it's brilliant.
It can't be terrible if Rolling Stone praised it, however.
Do you like teen comedies?
Not normally, but sometimes. Clueless was good, and DUFF, but there are still a bunch that are really terrible.

I'd say they're good about 35-40
% of the time.

When you watch the movie, note Lindsey's Lohan's character was actually homeschooled for sixteen years in Africa, before settling down in Evanston, Illinois where she attends public school for the first time
Sounds like it could be okay, I guess I'd try and see it.
But I don't think I'd be rushing or anything. How well did it do at the box office?
I currently don't have that information, but Rotten Tomatoes named it in its 'Top 50 Greatest Teen Comedies"
Oh, wow!
Rolling stone and rotten tomato love it? That sounds like it'd be a pretty iconic movie.

It did contain something called a "Burn Book" which you may have heard of. The "Burn Book" was fairly central to the plot. Although somewhat a negative portrayal of teenage girls, the "Burn Book" has also probably become iconic.
I've heard of that, definitely. That's the book where they write crappy messages about each other in it?
I agree, it does have a negative portrayal of teenage girls, however, with the internet and so many "anonymous" sites these days, it's not far off, unfortunately.
It isn't far off at all. The movie came out back in 2004 back when the Internet was a little younger.
The "Burn Book" even included things about the teachers
and of course Lindsey Lohan's character is at the center of all of it.
I do usually like my stories to be a bit more realistic, even if the reality of it is harsh.
Oh, isn't she always in the center of everything? LOL
Yes the was a very fitting role for a young Lindsey Lohan
But you might be surprised how it turns out
I might just check it out! Thanks!
You're welcome

uid2response.feedback: I think the user described the idea of the story fairly well, and made me feel comfortable enough with my decision. They even made sure to take my choice of  movie preferences in account, which was fantastic.
